HEADWORD: Hectare
<hw>Hec"tare`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. Gr. <?/
hundred + F. <ets>are</ets> an are.]</ety> <def>A measure of area, or
superficies, containing a hundred ares, or 10,000 square meters, and
equivalent to 2.471 acres.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hectic</ent>⟦br⟧
